calculateFastOdometry(ArrayList<Vec2d>) - Method in class com.mineinjava.quail.localization.SwerveOdometry
Calculates the robot's movement based on the module positions This is the recommended method to use if: - the sum of all the module placement vectors is (0, 0) - this means that the sum of each module's rotation vectors will equal (0, 0), so the average of the module vectors will be the robot movement vector Again, due to drift, it is recommended not to use the robot's rotation value given from this method.
